title: Walmex says same store sales rise 10.2 percent in September
text:
Walmex says same store sales rise 10.2 percent in September
1 Min Read
MEXICO CITY (Reuters) - Mexicoâ€™s biggest retailer, Wal-Mart de Mexico, said on Thursday that sales at its Mexican stores that have been open at least a year rose by 10.2 percent in September compared to the same month a year earlier.
Total sales increased by 12.0 percent on the year.
Reporting by Miguel Gutierrez
